  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bc8  835 \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bc1- \u0b8f\u0b8e\u0bb5\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ceylon Electricity Board has demanded an 835 percent increase in tariffs - AOP",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB) has demanded an 835 percent increase in electricity tariffs, according to AOP.",
        "The Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB), Sri Lanka's worst-hit state-owned monopoly on bankrupt fuel, has demanded a shocking 835 percent tariff increase from poor consumers, according to the Electricity Regulatory Commission.",
        "The South Asian country is badly affected by the foreign exchange deficit, with dollar shortages making it impossible to even import fuel for power generation and transportation.",
        "The Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB) has suffered a loss of 65 billion rupees in the first quarter of this year and has demanded an 835 percent increase in tariffs from over-subsidized small electricity buyers, according to the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka.",
        "At present, users of 30 kilowatts pay a monthly fee of Rs.",
        "Commission chairman Janakaratnanayake said most consumers could not afford such a massive price hike, adding that they had come up with the idea of \u200b\u200breceiving a direct subsidy from the treasury to increase (less than half) what they asked for.",
        "He said the public consumption tariff hike has not been decided yet but the tariffs for trade and industry will increase by 43 to 61 per cent."
      ],
